Installing dependencies:
    Python 2.7.x    - if you have system pyton (mac or linux) okay, if you have annaconda (okay) - otherwise https://www.continuum.io/downloads
    pandas - if you have anaconda okay, if not "$: pip install pandas"
    numpy - if you have anaconda okay, if not "$: pip install numpy"
    matplotlib - if you have anaconda okay, if not "$: git clone git://github.com/matplotlib/matplotlib.git" >> "$: cd matplotlib" >> "$: python setup.py install"
    plotly - "$: pip install plotly"
    tqdm - "$: pip install tqdm"

    N.B. All of those commands may need to be run as root depending on your system setup (UNIX-Like: Sudo, NT: allow administrative access)

Getting Files:
    "$: git clone https://github.com/tboudreaux/PythonMasterClass.git" or if you don't have git go to https://github.com/tboudreaux/PythonMasterClass.git and download zip
